#: ../../../project/changelog.md:67
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} Added `pyxhr`, a synchronous HTTP client using XMLHttpRequest "
"that provides a requests-like API for making synchronous HTTP requests in "
"browser environments. This includes `XHRResponse` class and support for all "
"common HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, HEAD, PATCH, OPTIONS). {pr}"
"`5841`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:73
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} `pyfetch` now works when passed a JS Request object instead of "
"a url. {pr}`5866`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:76
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} The default behavior of `toJs()`/`to_js` was changed to "
"convert dictionaries to JavaScript objects. To opt into the old behavior, "
"pass `toJsLiteralMap: true` to `loadPyodide()`. This is deprecated. {pr}"
"`5912`"
msgstr ""

