msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added `headers` property to `pyodide.http.FetchResponse`. "
"{pr}`2078`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1058
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added `FetchResponse.text()` as a synonym to "
"`FetchResponse.string()` for better compatibility with other requests APIs. "
"{pr}`4052`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1062
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Changed the `FetchResponse` body getter methods to no longer "
"throw an `OSError` exception for 400 and above response status codes. Added "
"`FetchResponse.raise_for_status` to raise an `OSError` for error status "
"codes. {pr}`3986` {pr}`4053`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1069
msgid "{{ Performance }} Improved performance of PyProxy creation. {pr}`4096`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1072
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Fixed adding getters/setters to a `PyProxy` with `Object."
"defineProperty` and improved compliance with JavaScript rules around Proxy "
"traps. {pr}`4033`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1077
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} The promise methods `then`, `catch` and `finally_` are now "
"present also on `Task`s as well as `Future`s. {pr}`3748`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1081
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added methods to a `PyProxy` of a `list` to make these "
"work as drop-in replacements for JavaScript Arrays. {pr}`3853`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1085
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} When a `JsProxy` of an array is passed to Python builtin "
"functions that use the `PySequence_*` APIs, it now works as expected. Also "
"`jsarray * n` repeats the array `n` times and `jsarray + iterable` returns a "
"new array with the result values from the iterable appended. {pr}`3904`"
msgstr ""

