#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1233
msgid "_March 30, 2023_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1237
msgid ""
"{{ Update }} Pyodide now runs Python 3.11.2 which officially supports "
"WebAssembly as a [PEP11 Tier 3](https://peps.python.org/pep-0011/#tier-3) "
"platform. {pr}`3252`, {pr}`3614`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1241
msgid ""
"{{ Update }} We now build libpyodide.a so the Pyodide foreign function "
"interface can be experimentally linked into other Emscripten builds of "
"Python. {pr}`3335`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1245
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Updated Emscripten to version 3.1.32 {pr}`3471`, {pr}"
"`3517`, {pr}`3599`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1250
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Type exports of `PyProxy` subtypes have been moved from "
"`pyodide` to `pyodide/ffi` and many of them have changed names. The original "
"exports are still available but they are deprecated. {pr}`3523`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1255
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} The methods for checking `PyProxy` capabilities (e.g., "
"`supportsHas`, `isCallable`) are now deprecated. Use e.g., `instanceof "
"pyodide.ffi.PyCallable` instead. {pr}`3523`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1260
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added subclasses of `PyProxy` for each mixin. These can be "
"used to check whether a `PyProxy` supports a given set of methods with "
"`instanceof` e.g., `x instanceof pyodide.ffi.PyDict`. {pr}`3523`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1265
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added `stdLibURL` parameter to `loadPyodide` allowing to "
"customize the URL from which the Python standard library is loaded. {pr}"
"`3670`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1269
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Checking whether an object is an instance of a `PyProxy` "
"now only recognizes a `PyProxy` generated from the same Python interpreter. "
"This means that creating multiple interpreters and importing a `PyProxy` "
"from one into another no longer causes a fatal error. {pr}`3545`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1275
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `as_object_map` now accepts a keyword argument "
"`hereditary`. If set to `True` and indexing the object returns a plain-old-"
"object, then the return value will be automatically mapped in "
"`as_object_map` as well. {pr}`3638`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1280
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} A `JsProxy` of a JavaScript error object can be directly "
"thrown as Python exceptions. Previously Pyodide automatically wrapped them "
"in a `JsException` but that is no longer needed -- now `JsException` "
"inherits from both `JsProxy` and `Exception`. {pr}`3455`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1286
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `runPython` and `runPythonAsync` now accept a `locals` "
"argument. {pr}`3618`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1290
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Calling `loadPyodide` repeatedly in Node no longer results in "
"`MaxListenersExceededWarning`. Also, calling `loadPyodide` in Node v14 no "
"longer changes unhandled rejections in promises. {pr}`3542`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1295
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} If the `locals` argument to `eval_code` or `eval_code_async` is "
"`None` it now uses `locals=globals` as the documentation says. {pr}`3580`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1299
msgid "Python standard library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1301
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Unvendored `_pydecimal` and `pydoc_data` from the standard "
"library. Now these modules need to be loaded with `pyodide.loadPackage` or "
"`micropip.install`, or auto-loaded via imports in `pyodide.runPythonAsync` "
"{pr}`3525`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1306
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Test files of stdlib `ctypes` and `unittest` are now moved to "
"`test/ctypes` and `test/unittest` respectively. This change is adapted from "
"[CPython 3.12](https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/93839). {pr}`3507`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1313
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Pyodide no longer uses Emscripten preload plugin, hence "
"`pyodide.asm.data` is removed, in favor of `python_stdlib.zip`. This change "
"normally shouldn't affect users, but if you were using this file in a "
"bundler, you will need to remove it. {pr}`3584`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1318
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} `pyodide_py.tar` file is removed. This change normally "
"shouldn't affect users, but if you were using this file in a bundler, you "
"will need to remove it. {pr}`3621`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1323
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Python standard libraries are now vendored in a zipfile: `/"
"lib/python{version}.zip` in the in-browser MEMFS file system. If you need to "
"access the standard library source code, you need to unpack the zip file. "
"For example: `import shutil; shutil.unpack_archive('/lib/python311.zip', '/"
"lib/python3.11', 'zip)` {pr}`3584`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1330
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Improves the compression of wheel files with the JsDelivr CDN. For "
"browsers that support the Brotli compression (most modern ones) this should "
"result in a size reduction of 20-30%. Also most many `pyodide` CLI sub-"
"commands now support `--compression-level` as an optional parameter. {pr}"
"`3655`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1336
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Following libraries are now not linked to the Pyodide main "
"module: `libgl`, `libal`, `libhtml5`. This normally shouldn't affect users, "
"but if you are using these libraries in a package that are built out-of-"
"tree, you will need to link them to the package manually. {pr}`3505`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1344
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} PyProxies of Async iterators are now async iterable JavaScript "
"objects. The code:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1347
msgid ""
"for await (let x of async_iterator_pyproxy) {\n"
"  // ...\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1353
msgid ""
"would previously fail with `TypeError: async_iterator_pyproxy is not async "
"iterable`. (Python async _iterables_ that were not also iterators were "
"already async iterable, the problem was only with Python objects that are "
"both async _iterable_ and an async iterator.) {pr}`3708`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1359
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} A py-compiled build which has smaller and faster-to-load "
"packages is now deployed under `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/pyodide/v0.23.0/pyc/"
"` (also for future versions). The exceptions obtained with this builds will "
"not include code snippets however. {pr}`3701`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1365
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Removed support for calling functions from the root of "
"`pyodide` package directly. This has been deprecated since v0.21.0. Now all "
"functions are only available under submodules. {pr}`3677`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1370
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Removed support for passing the \"message\" argument to "
"`PyProxy.destroy` in a positional argument. This has been deprecated since "
"v0.22.0. {pr}`3677`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1374
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Python does not allow reserved words to be used as "
"attributes. For instance, `Array.from` is a `SyntaxError`. (JavaScript has a "
"more robust parser which can handle this.) To handle this, if an attribute "
"to a `JsProxy` consists of a Python reserved word followed by one or more "
"underscores, we remove a single underscore from the end of the attribute. "
"For instance, `Array.from_` would access `from` on the underlying JavaScript "
"object, whereas `o.from__` accesses the `from_` attribute. {pr}`3617`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1385
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} When building meta-packages (`core` and `min-scipy-stack`), "
"you must prefix `tag:` to the meta-package name. For example, to build the "
"`core` meta-package, you must run `pyodide build-recipes tag:core`, or "
"`PYODIDE_PACKAGES=\"tag:core\" make`. {pr}`3444`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1391
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement}} Add `--build-dependencies` to `pyodide build` command to "
"fetch and build dependencies of a package being built. Also adds `--skip-"
"dependency` to ignore selected dependencies. {pr}`3310`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1396
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement}} Added `pyodide build` support for building a list of "
"packages from a requirements.txt file with `pyodide build -r <requirements."
"txt>`. Also can output a list of chosen dependencies in the same format when "
"building a package and dependencies using the `--output-lockfile <lockfile."
"txt>` argument. This enables repeatable builds of packages. {pr}`3469`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1403
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added `package/tag` key to the `meta.yaml` spec to group "
"packages. {pr}`3444`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1407
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `pyodide build-recipes` now autodetects the number of CPU "
"cores in the system and uses them for parallel builds. {pr}`3559` {pr}`3598`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1411
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Fixed pip install error when installing cross build environment. "
"{pr}`3562`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1414
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Response files are now correctly handled when calculating "
"exported symbols. {pr}`3645`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1418
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Fix occasional build failure when building rust packages. {pr}"
"`3607`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1421
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Improved logging in `pyodide-build` with rich. {pr}`3442`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1424
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `pyodide build-recipes` now accepts `--no-deps` parameter, "
"which skips building dependencies of the package. This replaces `pyodide-"
"build buildpkg`. {pr}`3520`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1428
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} `pyodide build-recipes` now works out-of-tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1432
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} Removed deprecated CLI entrypoints `pyodide-build buildall` "
"which is replaced by `pyodide build-recipes`, and `pyodide-build mkpkg` "
"which is replaced by `pyodide skeleton pypi` {pr}`3668`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1436
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} Added `pyodide py-compile` CLI command that py compiles a "
"wheel or a zip file, converting .py files to .pyc files. It can also be "
"applied to a folder with wheels / zip files. If the input folder contains "
"the `repodata.json` the paths and checksums it contains will also be updated "
"{pr}`3253` {pr}`3700`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1442
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} Added `pyodide create-zipfile` CLI command that creates a zip "
"file of a directory. This command is hidden by default since it is not "
"intended for use by end users. {pr}`3411` {pr}`3463`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1447 ../../../project/changelog.md:2057
#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2356 ../../../project/changelog.md:2982
msgid "REPL"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1449
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Non-breaking space characters are now automatically converted to "
"regular spaces in pyodide REPL. {pr}`3558`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1453
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Allow changing the build type used in the REPL by passing "
"the `build` argument to the REPL URL. For instance, `https://pyodide.org/en/"
"latest/console.html?build=debug` will load debug dev build. {pr}`3671`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1460
msgid ""
"New packages: fastparquet {pr}`3590`, cramjam {pr}`3590`, pynacl {pr}`3500`, "
"pyxel {pr}`3508`. mypy {pr}`3504`, multidict {pr}`3581`, yarl {pr}`3702`, "
"idna {pr}`3702`, cbor-diag {pr}`3581`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1465
msgid ""
"Upgraded to micropip 0.3.0 (see [changelog](https://github.com/pyodide/"
"micropip/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md) {pr}`3709`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1469
msgid ""
"Added experimental [support for SDL based packages](using-sdl) {pr}`3508`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:1471
msgid ""
"Upgraded packages: see the list of packages versions in this release in {ref}"
"`packages-in-pyodide`."
msgstr ""

