#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2193
msgid ""
"[See the release notes for a summary.](https://blog.pyodide.org/posts/0.20-"
"release/)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2195
msgid "CPython and stdlib"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2197
msgid "{{ Update }} Pyodide now runs Python 3.10.2. {pr}`2225`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2200
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} All `ctypes` tests pass now except for "
"`test_callback_too_many_args` (and we have a plan to fix "
"`test_callback_too_many_args` upstream). `libffi-emscripten` now also passes "
"all libffi tests. {pr}`2350`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2208
msgid "{{Fix}} matplotlib now loads multiple fonts correctly {pr}`2271`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2210
msgid ""
"New packages: boost-histogram {pr}`2174`, cryptography v3.3.2 {pr}`2263`, "
"the standard library ssl module {pr}`2263`, python-solvespace v3.0.7, lazy-"
"object-proxy {pr}`2320`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2214
msgid ""
"Many more scipy linking errors were fixed, mostly related to the Fortran f2c "
"ABI for string arguments. There are still some fatal errors in the Scipy "
"test suite, but none seem to be simple linker errors. {pr}`2289`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2219
msgid ""
"Removed pyodide-interrupts. If you were using this for some reason, use "
"`pyodide.setInterruptBuffer` instead. {pr}`2309`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2223
msgid ""
"Most included packages were updated to the latest version. See {ref}"
"`packages-in-pyodide` for a full list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2226 ../../../project/changelog.md:2350
msgid "Type translations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2228
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Python tracebacks now include Javascript frames when Python calls a "
"Javascript function. {pr}`2123`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2232
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added a `default_converter` argument to `JsProxy.to_py` and "
"`pyodide.toPy` which is used to process any object that doesn't have a built-"
"in conversion to Python. Also added a `default_converter` argument to "
"`PyProxy.toJs` and `pyodide.ffi.to_js` to convert. {pr}`2170` and {pr}`2208`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2238
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Async Python functions called from Javascript now have the "
"resulting coroutine automatically scheduled. For instance, this makes it "
"possible to use an async Python function as a Javascript event handler. {pr}"
"`2319`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2243
msgid "Javascript package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2245
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} It is no longer necessary to provide `indexURL` to "
"`loadPyodide`. {pr}`2292`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2249
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} The `globals` argument to `pyodide.runPython` and `pyodide."
"runPythonAsync` is now passed as a named argument. The old usage still works "
"with a deprecation warning. {pr}`2300`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2254
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} The Javascript package was migrated to Typescript. {pr}"
"`2130` and {pr}`2133`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2257
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Fix importing pyodide with ESM syntax in a module type web worker. "
"{pr}`2220`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2260
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} When Pyodide is loaded as an ES6 module, no global "
"`loadPyodide` variable is created (instead, it should be accessed as an "
"attribute on the module). {pr}`2249`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2265
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} The type `Py2JsResult` has been replaced with `any` which is more "
"accurate. For backwards compatibility, we still export `Py2JsResult` as an "
"alias for `any`. {pr}`2277`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2270
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Pyodide now loads correctly even if requirejs is included. {pr}`2283`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2273
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added robust handling for non-`Error` objects thrown by "
"Javascript code. This mostly should never happen since well behaved "
"Javascript code ought to throw errors. But it's better not to completely "
"crash if it throws something else. {pr}`2294`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2279
msgid "pyodide_build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2281
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Pyodide now uses Python wheel files to distribute packages "
"rather than the emscripten `file_packager.py` format. {pr}`2027`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2285
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Pyodide now uses `pypa/build` to build packages. We (mostly) "
"use build isolation, so we can build packages that require conflicting "
"versions of setuptools or alternative build backends. {pr}`2272`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2290
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Most pure Python packages were switched to use the wheels "
"directly from PyPI rather than rebuilding them. {pr}`2126`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2294
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added support for C++ exceptions in packages. Now C++ "
"extensions compiled and linked with `-fexceptions` can catch C++ exceptions. "
"Furthermore, uncaught C++ exceptions will be formatted in a human-readable "
"way. {pr}`2178`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2300
msgid ""
"{{Breaking}} Removed the `skip-host` key from the `meta.yaml` format. If "
"needed, install a host copy of the package with pip instead. {pr}`2256`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2304 ../../../project/changelog.md:2566
msgid "Uncategorized"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2306
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} The interrupt buffer can be used to raise all 64 signals "
"now, not just `SIGINT`. Write a number between `1<= signum <= 64` into the "
"interrupt buffer to trigger the corresponding signal. By default everything "
"but `SIGINT` will be ignored. Any value written into the interrupt buffer "
"outside of the range from 1 to 64 will be silently discarded. {pr}`2301`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2313
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Updated to Emscripten 2.0.27. {pr}`2295`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2316
msgid ""
"{{ Breaking }} The `extractDir` argument to `pyodide.unpackArchive` is now "
"passed as a named argument. The old usage still works with a deprecation "
"warning. {pr}`2300`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2321
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Support ANSI escape codes in the Pyodide console. {pr}"
"`2345`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2324
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} `pyodide_build` can now be installed in non-editable ways. {pr}"
"`2351`"
msgstr ""

