msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2368
msgid "_January 10, 2021_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2370
msgid ""
"[See the release notes for a summary.](https://blog.pyodide.org/posts/0.19-"
"release/)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2372 ../../../project/changelog.md:2616
#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2713
msgid "Python package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2374
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} If `find_imports` is used on code that contains a syntax "
"error, it will return an empty list instead of raising a `SyntaxError`. {pr}"
"`1819`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2378
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added the `pyodide.http.pyfetch` API which provides a "
"convenience wrapper for the Javascript `fetch` API. The API returns a "
"response object with various methods that convert the data into various "
"types while minimizing the number of times the data is copied. {pr}`1865`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2384
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added the `unpack_archive` API to the `pyodide.http."
"FetchResponse` object which treats the response body as an archive and uses "
"`shutil` to unpack it. {pr}`1935`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2388
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} The Pyodide event loop now works correctly with cancelled handles. "
"In particular, `asyncio.wait_for` now functions as expected. {pr}`2022`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2392 ../../../project/changelog.md:2621
#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2689
msgid "JavaScript package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2394
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} `loadPyodide` no longer fails in the presence of a user-defined "
"global named `process`. {pr}`1849`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2398
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Various webpack buildtime and runtime compatibility issues were "
"fixed. {pr}`1900`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2401
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added the `pyodide.pyimport` API to import a Python module "
"and return it as a `PyProxy`. Warning: this is different from the original "
"`pyimport` API which was removed in this version. {pr}`1944`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2406
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added the `pyodide.unpackArchive` API which unpacks an "
"archive represented as an ArrayBuffer into the working directory. This is "
"intended as a way to install packages from a local application. {pr}`1944`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2411
msgid ""
"{{API}} `loadPyodide` now accepts a `homedir` parameter which sets home "
"directory of Pyodide virtual file system. {pr}`1936`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2415
msgid ""
"{{Breaking}} The default working directory(home directory) inside the "
"Pyodide virtual file system has been changed from `/` to `/home/pyodide`. To "
"get the previous behavior, you can"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2418
msgid "call `os.chdir(\"/\")` in Python to change working directory or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2419
msgid "call `loadPyodide` with the `homedir=\"/\"` argument {pr}`1936`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2423 ../../../project/changelog.md:2626
#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2732
msgid "Python / JavaScript type conversions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2425
msgid ""
"{{Breaking}} Updated the calling convention when a JavaScript function is "
"called from Python to improve memory management of PyProxies. PyProxy "
"arguments and return values are automatically destroyed when the function is "
"finished. {pr}`1573`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2431
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added `JsProxy.to_string`, `JsProxy.to_bytes`, and `JsProxy."
"to_memoryview` to allow for conversion of `TypedArray` to standard Python "
"types without unneeded copies. {pr}`1864`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2436
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added `JsProxy.to_file` and `JsProxy.from_file` to allow "
"reading and writing Javascript buffers to files as a byte stream without "
"unneeded copies. {pr}`1864`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2441
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} It is now possible to destroy a borrowed attribute `PyProxy` of a "
"`PyProxy` (as introduced by {pr}`1636`) before destroying the root "
"`PyProxy`. {pr}`1854`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2445
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} If `__iter__()` raises an error, it is now handled correctly by the "
"`PyProxy[Symbol.iterator()]` method. {pr}`1871`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2449
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Borrowed attribute `PyProxy`s are no longer destroyed when the root "
"`PyProxy` is garbage collected (because it was leaked). Doing so has no "
"benefit to nonleaky code and turns some leaky code into broken code (see "
"{issue}`1855` for an example). {pr}`1870`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2455
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Improved the way that `pyodide.globals.get(\"builtin_name\")` works. "
"Before we used `__main__.__dict__.update(builtins.__dict__)` which led to "
"several undesirable effects such as `__name__` being equal to "
"`\"builtins\"`. Now we use a proxy wrapper to replace `pyodide.globals.get` "
"with a function that looks up the name on `builtins` if lookup on `globals` "
"fails. {pr}`1905`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2462
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Coroutines have their memory managed in a more convenient "
"way. In particular, now it is only necessary to either `await` the coroutine "
"or call one of `.then`, `.except` or `.finally` to prevent a leak. It is no "
"longer necessary to manually destroy the coroutine. Example: before:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2467
msgid ""
"async function runPythonAsync(code, globals) {\n"
"  let coroutine = Module.pyodide_py.eval_code_async(code, globals);\n"
"  try {\n"
"    return await coroutine;\n"
"  } finally {\n"
"    coroutine.destroy();\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2478
msgid "After:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2480
msgid ""
"async function runPythonAsync(code, globals) {\n"
"  return await Module.pyodide_py.eval_code_async(code, globals);\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2486
msgid "{pr}`2030`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2488 ../../../project/changelog.md:2776
msgid "pyodide-build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2490
msgid ""
"{{API}} By default only a minimal set of packages is built. To build all "
"packages set `PYODIDE_PACKAGES='*'` In addition, `make minimal` was removed, "
"since it is now equivalent to `make` without extra arguments. {pr}`1801`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2495
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} It is now possible to use `pyodide-build buildall` and "
"`pyodide-build buildpkg` directly. {pr}`2063`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2499
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added a `--force-rebuild` flag to `buildall` and `buildpkg` "
"which rebuilds the package even if it looks like it doesn't need to be "
"rebuilt. Added a `--continue` flag which keeps the same source tree for the "
"package and can continue from the middle of a build. {pr}`2069`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2505
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Changes to environment variables in the build script are now "
"seen in the compile and post build scripts. {pr}`1706`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2509
msgid "{{Fix}} Fix usability issues with `pyodide-build mkpkg` CLI. {pr}`1828`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2512
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Better support for ccache when building Pyodide {pr}`1805`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2515
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Fix compile error `wasm-ld: error: unknown argument: --sort-common` "
"and `wasm-ld: error: unknown argument: --as-needed` in ArchLinux. {pr}`1965`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2519 ../../../project/changelog.md:2782
#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2942
msgid "micropip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2521
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} micropip now raises an error when installing a non-pure python wheel "
"directly from a url. {pr}`1859`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2525
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} {func}`micropip.install` now accepts a `keep_going` "
"parameter. If set to `True`, micropip reports all identifiable dependencies "
"that don't have pure Python wheels, instead of failing after processing the "
"first one. {pr}`1976`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2530
msgid ""
"{{Enhancement}} Added a new API {func}`micropip.list` which returns the list "
"of installed packages by micropip. {pr}`2012`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2536
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Unit tests are now unvendored from Python packages and "
"included in a separate package `<package name>-tests`. This results in a 20% "
"size reduction on average for packages that vendor tests (e.g. numpy, "
"pandas, scipy). {pr}`1832`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2542
msgid ""
"{{ Update }} Upgraded SciPy to 1.7.3. There are known issues with some SciPy "
"components, the current status of the scipy test suite is [here](https://"
"github.com/pyodide/pyodide/pull/2065#issuecomment-1004243045) {pr}`2065`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2547
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} The built-in pwd module of Python, which provides a Unix specific "
"feature, is now unvendored. {pr}`1883`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2551
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} pillow and imageio now correctly encode/decode grayscale and black-"
"and-white JPEG images. {pr}`2028`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2555
msgid "{{Fix}} The numpy fft module now works correctly. {pr}`2028`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2558
msgid ""
"New packages: logbook {pr}`1920`, pyb2d {pr}`1968`, and threadpoolctl (a "
"dependency of scikit-learn) {pr}`2065`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2561
msgid ""
"Upgraded packages: numpy (1.21.4) {pr}`1934`, scikit-learn (1.0.2) {pr}"
"`2065`, scikit-image (0.19.1) {pr}`2005`, msgpack (1.0.3) {pr}`2071`, "
"astropy (5.0.3) {pr}`2086`, statsmodels (0.13.1) {pr}`2073`, pillow (9.0.0) "
"{pr}`2085`. This list is not exhaustive, refer to `packages.json` for the "
"full list."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2568
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `PyErr_CheckSignals` now works with the keyboard interrupt "
"system so that cooperative C extensions can be interrupted. Also, added the "
"`pyodide.checkInterrupt` function so Javascript code can opt to be "
"interrupted. {pr}`1294`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2574
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} The `_` variable is now set by the Pyodide repl just like it is set "
"in the native Python repl. {pr}`1904`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2578
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `pyodide-env` and `pyodide` Docker images are now "
"available from both the [Docker Hub](https://hub.docker.com/repository/"
"docker/pyodide/pyodide-env) and from the [Github Package registry](https://"
"github.com/orgs/pyodide/packages). {pr}`1995`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2582
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} The console now correctly handles it when an object's `__repr__` "
"function raises an exception. {pr}`2021`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2585
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Removed the `-s EMULATE_FUNCTION_POINTER_CASTS` flag, "
"yielding large benefits in speed, stack usage, and code size. {pr}`2019`"
msgstr ""

