msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2628
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Conversion of very large strings from JavaScript to Python works "
"again. {pr}`1806`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2631
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Fixed a use after free bug in the error handling code. {pr}`1816`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2636
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} pillow now correctly encodes/decodes RGB JPEG image format. {pr}"
"`1818`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2638
msgid "Micellaneous"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2640
msgid ""
"{{Fix}} Patched emscripten to make the system calls to duplicate file "
"descriptors closer to posix-compliant. In particular, this fixes the use of "
"`dup` on pipes and temporary files, as needed by `pytest`. {pr}`1823`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2645
msgid "Version 0.18.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2647
msgid "_August 3rd, 2021_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2651
msgid "{{ Update }} Pyodide now runs Python 3.9.5. {pr}`1637`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2654
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Pyodide can experimentally be used in Node.js {pr}`1689`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2656
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Pyodide now directly exposes the [Emscripten filesystem "
"API](https://emscripten.org/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.html), "
"allowing for direct manipulation of the in-memory filesystem {pr}`1692`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2661
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Pyodide's support of [emscripten file systems](https://"
"emscripten.org/docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#file-systems) is "
"expanded from the default `MEMFS` to include `IDBFS`, `NODEFS`, `PROXYFS`, "
"and `WORKERFS`, allowing for custom persistence strategies depending on "
"execution environment {pr}`1596`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2667
msgid ""
"{{ API }} The `packages.json` schema for Pyodide was redesigned for better "
"compatibility with conda. {pr}`1700`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2670
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `run_docker` no longer binds any port to the docker image by "
"default. {pr}`1750`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2673
msgid "Standard library"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2675
msgid ""
"{{ API }} The following standard library modules are now available as "
"standalone packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2676
msgid "distlib"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2678
msgid ""
"They are loaded by default in `loadPyodide`, however this behavior can be "
"disabled with the `fullStdLib` parameter set to `false`. All optional stdlib "
"modules can then be loaded as needed with `pyodide.loadPackage`. {pr}`1543`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2683
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} The standard library module `audioop` is now included, "
"making the `wave`, `sndhdr`, `aifc`, and `sunau` modules usable. {pr}`1623`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2686
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Added support for `ctypes`. {pr}`1656`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2691
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} The Pyodide JavaScript package is released to npm under "
"[npmjs.com/package/pyodide](https://www.npmjs.com/package/pyodide) {pr}`1762`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2693
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `loadPyodide` no longer automatically stores the API into a global "
"variable called `pyodide`. To get old behavior, say `globalThis.pyodide = "
"await loadPyodide({...})`. {pr}`1597`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2697
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `loadPyodide` now accepts callback functions for `stdin`, "
"`stdout` and `stderr` {pr}`1728`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2700
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Pyodide now ships with first party typescript types for "
"the entire JavaScript API (though no typings are available for `PyProxy` "
"fields). {pr}`1601`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2704
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} It is now possible to import `Comlink` objects into "
"Pyodide after using `pyodide.registerComlink` {pr}`1642`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2708
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} If a Python error occurs in a reentrant `runPython` call, "
"the error will be propagated into the outer `runPython` context as the "
"original error type. This is particularly important if the error is a "
"`KeyboardInterrupt`. {pr}`1447`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2715
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added a new `pyodide.code.CodeRunner` API for finer "
"control than `eval_code` and `eval_code_async`. Designed with the needs of "
"REPL implementations in mind. {pr}`1563`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2720
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added `pyodide.console.Console` class closely based on the "
"Python standard library `code.InteractiveConsole` but with support for top "
"level await and stream redirection. Also added the subclass `pyodide.console."
"PyodideConsole` which automatically uses `pyodide.loadPackagesFromImports` "
"on the code before running it. {pr}`1125`, {pr}`1155`, {pr}`1635`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2727
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} `pyodide.code.eval_code_async` no longer automatically awaits a "
"returned coroutine or attempts to await a returned generator object (which "
"triggered an error). {pr}`1563`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2734
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `pyodide.runPythonAsync` no longer automatically calls `pyodide."
"loadPackagesFromImports`. {pr}`1538`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2737
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added the `PyProxy.callKwargs` method to allow using "
"Python functions with keyword arguments from JavaScript. {pr}`1539`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2740
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Added the `PyProxy.copy` method. {pr}`1549` {pr}`1630`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2742
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Updated the method resolution order on `PyProxy`. Performing a "
"lookup on a `PyProxy` will prefer to pick a method from the `PyProxy` api, "
"if no such method is found, it will use `getattr` on the proxied object. "
"Prefixing a name with `$` forces `getattr`. For instance, `PyProxy.destroy` "
"now always refers to the method that destroys the proxy, whereas `PyProxy."
"$destroy` refers to an attribute or method called `destroy` on the proxied "
"object. {pr}`1604`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2750
msgid ""
"{{ API }} It is now possible to use `Symbol` keys with PyProxies. These "
"`Symbol` keys put markers on the PyProxy that can be used by external code. "
"They will not currently be copied by `PyProxy.copy`. {pr}`1696`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2754
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Memory management of `PyProxy` fields has been changed so "
"that fields looked up on a `PyProxy` are \"borrowed\" and have their "
"lifetime attached to the base `PyProxy`. This is intended to allow for more "
"idiomatic usage. (See {issue}`1617`.) {pr}`1636`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2759
msgid ""
"{{ API }} The depth argument to `toJs` is now passed as an option, so "
"`toJs(n)` in v0.17 changed to `toJs({depth : n})`. Similarly, `pyodide.toPy` "
"now takes `depth` as a named argument. Also `to_js` and `to_py` only take "
"depth as a keyword argument. {pr}`1721`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2764
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `PyProxy.toJs` and `pyodide.ffi.to_js` now take an option "
"`pyproxies`, if a JavaScript Array is passed for this, then any proxies "
"created during conversion will be placed into this array. This allows easy "
"cleanup later. The `create_pyproxies` option can be used to disable creation "
"of pyproxies during conversion (instead a `ConversionError` is raised). {pr}"
"`1726`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2770
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `toJs` and `to_js` now take an option `dict_converter` which will "
"be called on a JavaScript iterable of two-element Arrays as the final step "
"of converting dictionaries. For instance, pass `Object.fromEntries` to "
"convert to an object or `Array.from` to convert to an array of pairs. {pr}"
"`1742`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2778
msgid ""
"{{ API }} pyodide-build is now an installable Python package, with an "
"identically named CLI entrypoint that replaces `bin/pyodide` which is "
"removed {pr}`1566`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2784
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} micropip now correctly handles packages that have mixed case "
"names. (See {issue}`1614`). {pr}`1615`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2787
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} micropip now resolves dependencies correctly for old "
"versions of packages (it used to always use the dependencies from the most "
"recent version, see {issue}`1619` and {issue}`1745`). micropip also will "
"resolve dependencies for wheels loaded from custom urls. {pr}`1753`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2795
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} matplotlib now comes with a new renderer based on the "
"html5 canvas element. {pr}`1579` It is optional and the current default "
"backend is still the agg backend compiled to wasm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2797
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Updated a number of packages included in Pyodide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2801
msgid ""
"Albertas Gimbutas, Andreas Klostermann, Arfy Slowy, daoxian, Devin Neal, "
"fuyutarow, Grimmer, Guido Zuidhof, Gyeongjae Choi, Hood Chatham, Ian "
"Clester, Itay Dafna, Jeremy Tuloup, jmsmdy, LinasNas, Madhur Tandon, Michael "
"Christensen, Nicholas Bollweg, OndĹ™ej StanÄ›k, Paul m. p. P, Piet BrĂ¶mmel, "
"Roman Yurchak, stefnotch, Syrus Akbary, Teon L Brooks, Waldir"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2807
msgid "Version 0.17.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2809
msgid "_April 21, 2021_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2811
msgid "See the {ref}`0-17-0-release-notes` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2813
msgid "Improvements to package loading and dynamic linking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2815
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Uses the emscripten preload plugin system to preload .so "
"files in packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2816
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Support for shared library packages. This is used for "
"CLAPACK which makes scipy a lot smaller. {pr}`1236`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2818
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Pyodide and included packages can now be used with Safari v14+. "
"Safari v13 has also been observed to work on some (but not all) devices."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2821 ../../../project/changelog.md:3039
msgid "Python / JS type conversions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2823
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} A `JsProxy` of a JavaScript `Promise` or other awaitable "
"object is now a Python awaitable. {pr}`880`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2826
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Instead of automatically converting Python lists and dicts into "
"JavaScript, they are now wrapped in `PyProxy`. Added a new `PyProxy.toJs` "
"API to request the conversion behavior that used to be implicit. {pr}`1167`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2830
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Added `JsProxy.to_py` API to convert a JavaScript object to "
"Python. {pr}`1244`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2832
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} Flexible jsimports: it now possible to add custom Python "
"\"packages\" backed by JavaScript code, like the `js` package. The `js` "
"package is now implemented using this system. {pr}`1146`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2836
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} A `PyProxy` of a Python coroutine or awaitable is now an "
"awaitable JavaScript object. Awaiting a coroutine will schedule it to run on "
"the Python event loop using `asyncio.ensure_future`. {pr}`1170`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2840
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Made `PyProxy` of an iterable Python object an iterable Js "
"object: defined the `[Symbol.iterator]` method, can be used like `for(let x "
"of proxy)`. Made a `PyProxy` of a Python iterator an iterator: `proxy."
"next()` is translated to `next(it)`. Made a `PyProxy` of a Python generator "
"into a JavaScript generator: `proxy.next(val)` is translated to `gen."
"send(val)`. {pr}`1180`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2846
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Updated `PyProxy` so that if the wrapped Python object supports "
"`__getitem__` access, then the wrapper has `get`, `set`, `has`, and `delete` "
"methods which do `obj[key]`, `obj[key] = val`, `key in obj` and `del "
"obj[key]` respectively. {pr}`1175`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2850
msgid ""
"{{ API }} The `pyodide.pyimport` function is deprecated in favor of using "
"`pyodide.globals.get('key')`. {pr}`1367`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2852
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Added `PyProxy.getBuffer` API to allow direct access to Python "
"buffers as JavaScript TypedArrays. {pr}`1215`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2855
msgid ""
"{{ API }} The innermost level of a buffer converted to JavaScript used to be "
"a TypedArray if the buffer was contiguous and otherwise an Array. Now the "
"innermost level will be a TypedArray unless the buffer format code is a '?' "
"in which case it will be an Array of booleans, or if the format code is a "
"\"s\" in which case the innermost level will be converted to a string. {pr}"
"`1376`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2861
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} JavaScript `BigInt`s are converted into Python `int` and "
"Python `int`s larger than 2^53 are converted into `BigInt`. {pr}`1407`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2864
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Added `pyodide.isPyProxy` to test if an object is a `PyProxy`. {pr}"
"`1456`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2866
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} `PyProxy` and `PyBuffer` objects are now garbage collected "
"if the browser supports `FinalizationRegistry`. {pr}`1306`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2869
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Automatic conversion of JavaScript functions to CPython "
"calling conventions. {pr}`1051`, {pr}`1080`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2872
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Automatic detection of fatal errors. In this case Pyodide "
"will produce both a JavaScript and a Python stack trace with explicit "
"instruction to open a bug report. pr`{1151}`, pr`{1390}`, pr`{1478}`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2876
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Systematic memory leak detection in the test suite and a "
"large number of fixed to memory leaks. pr`{1340}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2879
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} getattr and dir on JsProxy now report consistent results and "
"include all names defined on the Python dictionary backing JsProxy. {pr}"
"`1017`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2882
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} `JsProxy.__bool__` now produces more consistent results: both "
"`bool(window)` and `bool(zero-arg-callback)` were `False` but now are "
"`True`. Conversely, `bool(empty_js_set)` and `bool(empty_js_map)` were "
"`True` but now are `False`. {pr}`1061`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2887
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} When calling a JavaScript function from Python without keyword "
"arguments, Pyodide no longer passes a `PyProxy`-wrapped `NULL` pointer as "
"the last argument. {pr}`1033`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2890
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} JsBoundMethod is now a subclass of JsProxy, which fixes nested "
"attribute access and various other strange bugs. {pr}`1124`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2893
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} JavaScript functions imported like `from js import fetch` no "
"longer trigger \"invalid invocation\" errors (issue {issue}`461`) and `js."
"fetch(\"some_url\")` also works now (issue {issue}`768`). {pr}`1126`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2897
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} JavaScript bound method calls now work correctly with keyword "
"arguments. {pr}`1138`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2899
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} JavaScript constructor calls now work correctly with keyword "
"arguments. {pr}`1433`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2903
msgid "pyodide-py package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2905
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} Added a Python event loop to support asyncio by scheduling "
"coroutines to run as jobs on the browser event loop. This event loop is "
"available by default and automatically enabled by any relevant asyncio API, "
"so for instance `asyncio.ensure_future` works without any configuration. {pr}"
"`1158`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2910
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Removed `as_nested_list` API in favor of `JsProxy.to_py`. {pr}"
"`1345`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2913
msgid "pyodide-js"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2915
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Removed iodide-specific code in `pyodide.js`. This breaks "
"compatibility with iodide. {pr}`878`, {pr}`981`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2918
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Removed the `pyodide.autocomplete` API, use Jedi directly instead. "
"{pr}`1066`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2920
msgid "{{ API }} Removed `pyodide.repr` API. {pr}`1067`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2922
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} If `messageCallback` and `errorCallback` are supplied to `pyodide."
"loadPackage`, `pyodide.runPythonAsync` and `pyodide.loadPackagesFromImport`, "
"then the messages are no longer automatically logged to the console."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2926
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} `runPythonAsync` now runs the code with `eval_code_async`. In "
"particular, it is possible to use top-level await inside of `runPythonAsync`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2928
msgid ""
"`eval_code` now accepts separate `globals` and `locals` parameters. {pr}"
"`1083`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2930
msgid ""
"Added the `pyodide.setInterruptBuffer` API. This can be used to set a "
"`SharedArrayBuffer` to be the keyboard interrupt buffer. If Pyodide is "
"running on a webworker, the main thread can signal to the webworker that it "
"should raise a `KeyboardInterrupt` by writing to the interrupt buffer. {pr}"
"`1148` and {pr}`1173`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2935
msgid ""
"Changed the loading method: added an async function `loadPyodide` to load "
"Pyodide to use instead of `languagePluginURL` and `languagePluginLoader`. "
"The change is currently backwards compatible, but the old approach is "
"deprecated. {pr}`1363`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2939
msgid "`runPythonAsync` now accepts `globals` parameter. {pr}`1914`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2944
msgid ""
"{{ Feature }} `micropip` now supports installing wheels from relative URLs. "
"{pr}`872`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2946
msgid ""
"{{ API }} `micropip.install` now returns a Python `Future` instead of a "
"JavaScript `Promise`. {pr}`1324`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2948
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} `micropip.install` now interacts correctly with {js:func}`pyodide."
"loadPackage`. {pr}`1457`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2951
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} `micropip.install` now handles version constraints correctly even "
"if there is a version of the package available from the Pyodide `indexURL`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2956
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Updated to latest emscripten 2.0.13 with the upstream LLVM "
"backend {pr}`1102`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2958
msgid ""
"{{ API }} Use upstream `file_packager.py`, and stop checking package abi "
"versions. The `PYODIDE_PACKAGE_ABI` environment variable is no longer used, "
"but is still set as some packages use it to detect whether it is being built "
"for Pyodide. This usage is deprecated, and a new environment variable "
"`PYODIDE` is introduced for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2964
msgid "As part of the change, Module.checkABI is no longer present. {pr}`991`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2967
msgid ""
"uglifyjs and lessc no longer need to be installed in the system during build "
"{pr}`878`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2969
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Reduce the size of the core Pyodide package {pr}`987`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2971
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Optionally to disable docker port binding {pr}`1423`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2973
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Run arbitrary command in docker {pr}`1424`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2975
msgid ""
"Docker images for Pyodide are now accessible at [pyodide/pyodide-env]"
"(https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/pyodide/pyodide-env) and [pyodide/"
"pyodide](https://hub.docker.com/repository/docker/pyodide/pyodide)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2979
msgid ""
"{{ Enhancement }} Option to run docker in non-interactive mode {pr}`1641`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2984
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} In console.html: sync behavior, full stdout/stderr support, clean "
"namespace, bigger font, correct result representation, clean traceback {pr}"
"`1125` and {pr}`1141`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2987
msgid ""
"{{ Fix }} Switched from Ě€Jedi to rlcompleter for completion in `pyodide."
"console.InteractiveConsole` and so in `console.html`. This fixes some "
"completion issues (see {issue}`821` and {issue}`1160`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2990
msgid "{{ Enhancement }} Support top-level await in the console {pr}`1459`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../project/changelog.md:2995
msgid ""
"six, jedi and parso are no longer vendored in the main Pyodide package, and "
"need to be loaded explicitly {pr}`1010`, {pr}`987`."
